reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Compact, Colorful, and Customizable
reviews.reviewText: The ZIYOU LANG RK-T8 Wired 65% Mechanical Gaming Keyboard is a powerhouse of features packed into a compact and stylish design. Whether you're a gamer, a professional, or someone on the go, this keyboard offers an exceptional typing and gaming experience. Here's why I'm impressed with it:Portability is key, and the 65% layout of the keyboard delivers just that. With its compact design, it maximizes your workspace and allows for easy transportation. The charming color-matched keycaps add a touch of personality, making it a visually appealing choice. Additionally, the detachable custom C to A USB cable with a metal aviator enhances durability and convenience, ensuring a reliable connection.The keyboard features professional soldered mechanical Blue switches, renowned for their satisfying tactile feedback and audible click sound. This clicky switch provides an immersive typing experience, adding a delightful touch to every keystroke. The ergonomic NKRO keyboard supports non-conflicting key inputs, allowing for seamless and accurate keystrokes, whether you're gaming or working on urgent tasks.With its vibrant and groovy True RGB backlighting, the keyboard offers a range of customization options. Choose from 18 preset backlighting modes, 9 backlight colors, and adjust brightness and speed levels to match your preferences or gaming setup. The double-shot injection keycaps not only provide durability but also enhance the backlighting effect, making it a visual treat, especially in low-light environments.The keyboard comes with a high-quality spiral cable that adds flexibility and style. The USB Type-C to USB-A cable supports fast charging and data sync, ensuring a stable connection. Its versatility extends beyond the keyboard and is compatible with various devices such as mechanical gaming keyboards, printers, and game consoles like PS4 and Switch.Take control of your keyboard customization with the pro software that allows advanced customization options. Design your own lighting effects, set up macros, and personalize the keyboard to suit your preferences. The premier PCB board and good flash memory ensure optimal performance, while multimedia functions offer quick access to music and calculator. The keyboard is compatible with Windows, Android, Linux, and iOS systems.In summary, the ZIYOU LANG RK-T8 Wired 65% Mechanical Gaming Keyboard combines portability, functionality, and customization in a single package. Its compact design, clicky mechanical switches, vibrant RGB backlighting, and high-quality spiral cable make it a standout choice. Whether you're a gamer, a professional, or someone who appreciates a reliable and stylish keyboard, the ZIYOU LANG RK-T8 is a worthy investment.Unlock your gaming and typing potential with this feature-packed keyboard and enjoy the immersive experience it brings to your fingertips.

reviews.reviewText: Was skeptical with cheap keyboards, but this one has hot swap able keys, needs no 3party software, sounds great and the color scheme looks really good TBH.has FN1 and FN2 keys as the number keys have 3 different rows of keybinds. NOT KNOCKING any stars, (user error/issue)love the keyboard it actually replaced my more expensive Corsair keyboard as i like the size and sound.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Not the best quality, but more than good enough
reviews.reviewText: The keyboard feels slightly plasticky, and the keys bleed light, with the "dual injection" looking prettysloppy on a lot of keys.That being said, the keyboard is pretty nice all things considered, the price makes it easy to look past any shortcomings. The RGB's are nice, bonus points that you don't need to download or run any additional software, you can just control them from the keys themselves.The switch feel is decent, I wouldn't say it's anything to write home about but I would say it's definitely good enough. The sound could be better out of the box, it's also far from the worst. I put foam in the bottom of the casing, and without doing anything else the sound improved significantly on the same keys and switches. The switches are hot swappable too, which is awesome for a keyboard in this price range.I unfortunately won't be keeping this keyboard, because there's no "feet" on the back to adjust the angle, and I feel like it lays too flat for my personal preference, but all things considered you can do much worse than this keyboard.

reviews.reviewTitle: 9.4/10 im probably going to buy another one.
reviews.reviewText: the RGB is AMAZING. I left it on the default setting because i like it so much so i didnt try any other settings. this is my first 65% keyboard. also my first keyboard with red linear switchs, they feel amazing and consistant. The coiled cable is amazing and good quality. i dont mind the key colour at all. one final note. the space bar is loud and rattley but functions perfectly. i bought this key board to mod (lube, foam, tape, etc) and i think it a great starter keyboard if this is the size youre looking for. also i dont know if this is hot swapable or not as im not taking it apart yet. the white keys are snow white, the texture is what i like. at this price i might buy a few more and find some key caps for my other computers.came with board, cable, and key cap puller,RGB looks way better in person.UPDATE. The PCB is soldered. The switches are north facing.I won’t be desoldering it to lube the switches but you can still tape the PCB and band-aid the stabilizers if you’re super careful.
great keyboard nice and clicky. took me a year to figure out that ` is fn+esc, and ~ is fn+esc+shift. but that's cause im dumb.

As a budget-friendly keyboard, you are getting so much value out of it. I like the design and style of it. while the keyboard types click might be a load for some people I enjoy the sound of it.There are many different background colours to choose from, backlight options, and patterns that anyone can find an option they will enjoy.My only Frustration is as a Mac user there really isn't a Mac option when buying the Keyboard so switching commands between Mac and Windows was a learning curve and cost me more than I would have initially wanted.If you're doing a lot of work and need a high-end Keyboard then you probably won't want this one, but for anyone else, this is a great option and I would recommend it to most anyone.
